message: Wisdom teeth generally erupt between the ages of 17 and 19. Just because Rain Man says wisdom teeth erupt at the age of 25 does not mean they do. Rain Man is an intelligent man but he is not always correct about everything.

Here is a reliable source about wisdom teeth erupting around the ages of 16 to 19: https://www.sylvainchamberland.com/en/dentition-en/wisdom-teeth/

"Third molars are commonly called wisdom teeeth because they erupt in the mouth around 16-18 years of age."

It does not say 25 or 29 or 35 or 75. Wisdom teeth do not erupt in the 20s. The late teens are the latest ages that Wisdom Teeth can erupt.

Wisdom Teeth can erupt anywhere from 14 to 19 depending on the person's development. For some people, wisdom teeth will emerge some time between the ages of 17 and 19.  For most people Wisdom Teeth usually erupt around 16 to 18 years of age. Reference 1: https://www.sylvainchamberland.com/en/dentition-en/wisdom-teeth/ Reference 2: https://www.avasonfamilydentistry.com/blog/2018/11/28/wisdom-tooth-removal-and-age-195109

Some people like to believe that the wisdom teeth erupt around the ages of 21, 25, 35, 38 or even 80 in some cases. Some people also like to believe the Loch Ness monster is real. There are some people in the world who enjoy fantasies and enjoy trying to convince other people that they are real. However in reality the wisdom teeth can erupt anywhere from the ages of 14 to 19 years old depending on the person's physical development. But they usually erupt around 16 to 18 years old for most people
